'''CHY-MAX''' is Genetically Engineered bovine [[chymosin]] produced by the biotech company Chr. Hansen A/S. '''CHY-MAX''' is produced by fermentation of the fungus ''Aspergillus niger''. Bovine chymosin is an enzyme that causes [[milk]] to [[curdle]]. Being a non [[animal]] derived product, '''CHY-MAX''' is suitable for consumption by [[vegetarian]]s, as well as for production of cheese certified Kosher or Halal.

