'''Travel clinics''' are medical facilities that specialize in providing [[Preventive medicine|preventive medical care]] such as [[vaccination]]s or [[altitude sickness]] medicine to international travelers.<ref>[http://www.travelersvaccines.com TravelersVaccines.com, Consult a Travel Clinic<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The United States' [[Center for Disease Control]] publish recommended medical guidelines, the '''Yellow Book''', as a reference for physicians treating international travelers.<ref>[http://wwwn.cdc.gov/travel/contentYellowBook.aspx CDC Yellow Book]</ref> Immunizations recommended for international travel normally include Chicken Pox, Hepatitis A, Hepatitis B, Typhoid, Yellow Fever and Japanese Encephalitis.<ref>[http://www.travelclinicnyc.org Travel Clinic NYC]</ref><ref>[http://www.cmmediclinic.com/vaccinations.html Travel Vaccination Clinic Thailand]</ref>
